================================================================================
SENTINEL END-USER LICENSE AGREEMENT (EULA) & TERMS OF USE
================================================================================
Version 1.0
Last Updated: February 2026

I. SUMMARY OF YOUR AGREEMENT (TL;DR)

HARDWARE STRESS TEST: Sentinel tests your SD card by writing and reading data. This process involves physical wear on the hardware.

THE "LAST STRAW" RISK: If your card is already failing, running this test may cause it to fail immediately. You accept this risk.

NOT A REPAIR TOOL: Sentinel is an early warning system. It does not "fix" or "heal" bad cards.

EARLY RELEASE: This is beta software. It may contain bugs.

LIABILITY CAP: The developer's maximum liability to you is $1.00 USD.

LEGAL: All disputes are handled in Schenectady County, New York.

II. END-USER LICENSE AGREEMENT (EULA)

1. Grant of License
Phalanx Software Labs ("Licensor") grants a personal, non-exclusive, and limited license to use Sentinel ("Software") solely for personal, non-commercial hardware testing.

2. Acceptance of Terms
By clicking "I Agree" or by using the Software, you acknowledge that you have read and agree to these terms. You are required to manifest assent to these terms upon every launch.

3. Restrictions
No Redistribution: You may not redistribute or sell the Software.
No Reverse Engineering: You agree not to decompile or attempt to derive the source code.

III. TERMS OF USE & USER CONDUCT

4. User Responsibility for Data
Sentinel writes and deletes data during its "Quick" and "In-Depth" scans. You are solely responsible for backing up any existing data on the SD card before running a scan.

5. Privacy
Sentinel operates locally. We do not track your hardware IDs, scan results, or personal data.

IV. HARDWARE WARNINGS, WARRANTIES, AND LIABILITY

6. EXPRESS ASSUMPTION OF HARDWARE RISK (CRITICAL)
Stress Testing: You acknowledge that Sentinel performs "Write/Read" operations that consume the finite write cycles of flash memory.
Acceleration of Failure: You acknowledge that if a storage device is already degraded or failing, the stress of a Sentinel scan may accelerate its final failure.
No Recovery: Sentinel is a diagnostic tool, not a data recovery tool. It cannot recover lost data or repair physical sectors.
Assumption of Risk: By clicking "I Agree," you voluntarily assume all risks of hardware failure, data loss, or "bricked" SD cards resulting from the testing process.

7. ACCURACY OF ANALYSIS
While Sentinel is designed to provide an "Early Warning," no software can guarantee 100% accuracy in predicting hardware failure. A "Pass" result does not guarantee that a card will not fail in the future, and an 80% confidence level is an estimate, not a legal warranty.

8. DISCLAIMER OF WARRANTIES
THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS." THE DEVELOPER DISCLAIMS ALL WARRANTIES, INCLUDING MERCHANTABILITY AND FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE. THE DEVELOPER DOES NOT GUARANTEE THAT THE SCAN WILL IDENTIFY EVERY POSSIBLE HARDWARE DEFECT.

9. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY
IN NO EVENT SHALL THE DEVELOPER'S TOTAL LIABILITY EXCEED $1.00 USD. THE DEVELOPER SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR THE COST OF REPLACING FAILED SD CARDS OR FOR THE VALUE OF DATA LOST DURING A SCAN.

